The paper presents a novel RL algorithm that focuses on improving the robustness of RL agents. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in the field of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of generalization, which is a key issue in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses the MuJoCo simulator, which is commonly used in robotics and control research. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category.
